EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO ELECTIONS -- GENERAL STATE OFFICERS
***
1 This act would provide that for the general officers of the state, no person could be elected
2 to the same general office more than twice, and no person who has held a general office for more
3 than two (2) years of a term to which some other person was elected could be elected to the same
4 general office more than once. This act would further provide that a person who was ineligible to
5 be elected governor could not be elected lieutenant governor.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
